Package org.neo4j.internal.helpers.collection

Interface Visitor<E,​FAILURE extends Exception>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the element type the visitor accepts.
    FAILURE - the type of exception the visitor might throw
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    RecoveryApplier, TransactionApplier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CacheInvalidationTransactionApplier, ConsistencyCheckingApplierFactory.ConsistencyCheckingApplier, CountsStoreTransactionApplier, DefaultRecoveryService.RecoveryVisitor, FullLabelStream, FullRelationshipTypeStream, FullTokenStream, HighIdTransactionApplier, IndexTransactionApplierFactory.SingleTransactionApplier, LogEntryWriter.StorageCommandSerializer, MultipleIndexPopulator.EntityPopulationVisitor, NeoStoreTransactionApplier, PropertyCommandsExtractor, PropertyReader.SpecificValueVisitor, TransactionApplier.Adapter, TransactionApplierFacade
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Visitor<E,​FAILURE extends Exception>
    A visitor to internalize iteration.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      boolean visit​(E element)
      Invoked for each element in a collection.

    • Method Detail

      • visit

        boolean visit​(E element)
       throws FAILURE extends Exception
        Invoked for each element in a collection. Return true to terminate the iteration, false to continue.
        Parameters:
        element - an element from the collection.
        Returns:
        true to terminate the iteration, false to continue.
        Throws:
        FAILURE - exception thrown by the visitor
        FAILURE extends Exception
